Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20mini-card=20UI=20=E2=80=94=20sidebar=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?mount,=20theme-aware=20rendering,=20auto-refresh?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First visible, runnable code. After this commit, loading the fork in
Perchance shows a compact mini-card at the top of the sidebar
(above the 'new chat / character' button) with the user's avatar monogram,
display name, current level, XP progress, and a subtle gold progress bar.
Clicking logs a placeholder for now — the full hero card lands in the
next commit.

New modules:
- src/utils/dom.js: h(tag, attrs, children) element builder. Text always
  goes in via text nodes, never innerHTML. Handles event listeners,
  style objects, class names, booleans. Plus replaceContents() helper.
- src/utils/format.js: formatNumber (1,000 separators), formatPercent,
  getInitialFromName (Intl.Segmenter-aware for emoji), formatRelativeTime.
- src/stats/db.js: raw IndexedDB read wrapper. Opens window.dbName (falls
  back to 'chatbot-ui-v1'), reads characters/threads/messages/lore/misc
  stores. Read-only, tolerant of missing stores, never throws — returns
  empty arrays on any error so the card always renders.
- src/render/styles.js: CSS template string. Uses Perchance CSS variables
  (var(--box-color), var(--border-color), etc.) so the mini-card adapts
  to whatever theme the user has set. One constant warm-gold accent
  (#b9894a → #d8b36a gradient) for the XP bar — the single 'game' visual
  element we add.
- src/render/mini_card.js: createMiniCard({onOpen}) builds the DOM and
  returns an element with an update(vm) method. Avatar is a monogram
  when no image URL is set, falls back to background-image when one is.
  Keyboard-accessible (Enter/Space open), proper ARIA label.
- src/profile/styles_install.js: injects the stylesheet exactly once.
- src/profile/mount.js: waits for #leftColumn (up to 30s), injects the
  card as its first child. Idempotent — second call is a no-op.
- src/profile/index.js: entry point. Wires IDB -> stats -> XP/level ->
  view model -> card. Periodic 30s refresh + visibilitychange refresh.
  All errors swallowed with a single console.warn per session so Perchance
  itself is never broken by us.
- src/bootstrap.js: last in manifest. Calls start() on DOMContentLoaded
  or immediately if DOM is ready.

Tests (45 total, all green, +13 new):
- test/utils_format.test.mjs: 13 tests covering number formatting,
  percent clamping, initial-letter extraction (including empty/null/emoji),
  and relative-time boundaries.

Style decisions worth calling out:
- The mini-card uses 'font-family: inherit' — it blends into Perchance's
  type system rather than introducing its own fonts. The fancy display
  typography is reserved for the full hero card modal where it belongs.
- The warm-gold accent is intentionally NOT theme-variable-driven. It's
  the one recognizable visual signature the project adds. Everything
  around it adapts to the user's theme.
- Mount uses polling rather than MutationObserver. Simpler, predictable
  cleanup, 300ms worst-case latency. If we ever see re-injection issues
  in practice, a MutationObserver fallback can be added.

Bundle: 14 modules bundled, +36 KB net (our code), passes parse check.
